## Notification Types

| Type | Description | Trigger |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `new_post` | New post from creator | Creator publishes post |
| `new_subscriber` | New subscriber | Fan subscribes |
| `subscription_expiring` | Subscription expiring | 3 days before expiry |
| `payment_received` | Payment received | Tip/PPV/subscription |
| `new_message` | New DM | Message received |
| `kyc_approved` | KYC approved | Veriff callback |
| `payout_sent` | Payout processed | Weekly payout |
| `tip_received` | Tip received | Fan sends tip |
| `comment_reply` | Comment reply | Reply to comment |

---

## Database Schema

Uses existing `notifications` table:
- `id` (UUID)
- `userId` (UUID, FK to users)
- `type` (VARCHAR 50)
- `title` (VARCHAR 255)
- `body` (TEXT, nullable)
- `data` (JSONB)
- `isRead` (BOOLEAN)
- `readAt` (TIMESTAMP, nullable)
- `actionUrl` (TEXT, nullable)
- `createdAt` (TIMESTAMP)

**Indexes:**
- `userId`
- `isRead`
- `createdAt` (DESC)
- Composite: `userId, isRead, createdAt`

---

## Architecture Compliance

✅ Follows Repository → Service → Controller pattern  
✅ No business logic in routes  
✅ No DB access in controllers  
✅ Proper error handling  
✅ Input validation  

